  ],
  "notes": [
    "This profile reserves the GPIO set used by the official CT117E-M4 LCD reference project, so unrelated modules will not silently steal the board LCD pins.",
    "The profile also provides exact board-level pin preferences for the LCD parallel bus and for the board I2C bus on PB6/PB7.",
    "The official four push-buttons are wired to PB0, PB1, PB2, and PB14, so the generic key_bank_4_gpio module can be used as the on-board key bank with active-low inputs.",
    "The on-board 8-LED bank is driven through an SN74HC573 latch: PC8-PC15 provide the latched data bits and PD2 is the latch-enable signal.",
    "Because the LED latch shares PC8-PC15 with the LCD high data byte, the board-specific LED helper keeps those bus pins fixed instead of reallocating them.",
    "Keep using explicit pin options if your training setup disconnects the on-board LCD or rewires the official daughterboard resources."
  ],
  "sources": [
    "CT117E-M4 product manual PDF",
